revised_title: Case Study: Bones of a Foetus Discharged Through an Ulcer Near the Navel
tldr: A woman in Lincolnshire experienced a rare case where the bones of a fetus were discharged through an ulcer near her navel. The fetus had been in her womb for about four and a half years before being expelled. The woman eventually recovered and went on to have another healthy child. This case study demonstrates the remarkable capabilities of nature and the human body.
